            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Introduced in November 2024, Google's site reputation abuse policy targets third-party content produced primarily for ranking purposes on high-authority domains. Host platforms that allow this content face ranking penalties for the offending pages or their entire site. It directly addresses the parasite SEO practice of placing ranking-optimised content on news sites and high-DA platforms.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What's the alternative to parasite SEO?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
